# Engineering Journal 003

## Question

What happens to an existing Kafka topic when one controller in a two-node KRaft cluster becomes unavailable?

## Initial Observation

After stopping Broker 2:

- Broker 1 became leader for all partitions.
- ISR contained only Broker 1.
- Broker logs repeatedly showed:

In the new epoch 3803, the leader is (none).

INFO [RaftManager id=1] Election has timed out, backing off for 1000ms before becoming a candidate again (org.apache.kafka.raft.KafkaRaftClient) kafka-1 | [2026-07-14 18:06:12,357] INFO [RaftManager id=1] Re-elect as candidate after election backoff has completed (org.apache.kafka.raft.KafkaRaftClient) kafka-1 | [2026-07-14 18:06:12,387] INFO [RaftManager id=1] Completed transition to CandidateState(localId=1, localDirectoryId=CRBTiGNARuarv-k7hW3w1w,epoch=3803, retries=344, voteStates={1=GRANTED, 2=UNRECORDED}, highWatermark=Optional.empty, electionTimeoutMs=1825) from CandidateState(localId=1, localDirectoryId=CRBTiGNARuarv-k7hW3w1w,epoch=3802, retries=343, voteStates={1=GRANTED, 2=UNRECORDED}, highWatermark=Optional.empty, electionTimeoutMs=1439) (org.apache.kafka.raft.QuorumState) kafka-1 | [2026-07-14 18:06:12,387] INFO [QuorumController id=1] In the new epoch 3803, the leader is (none).
